thread.title: Dollar Creeps Lower After Jobs Report

author: Ira Iosebashvili
title: Dollar Creeps Lower After Jobs Report
text:
The dollar edged lower Friday as investors looked past big job gains in Februaryâ€™s U.S. employment report to focus on anemic wage growth.
The WSJ Dollar Index, which measures the U.S. currency against a basket of 16 others, was recently down less than 0.1% at 83.84. The measure climbed, then dipped, after jobs data was released Friday morning.
